---
const PEOPLE = [
  "My Mom",
  "My Dad",
  "My Grandfather",
  "My Teachers",
  "Dr. Homi Bhabha",
  "Abdul Kalam",
  "Sachin Tendulkar",
  "Virat Kohli",
  "Javed Akhtar",
  "Zakir Khan",
  "Robin Sharma",
  "Akshay Kambli",
  "Shailesh Tyagi",
  "Raja Sandhu",
  "Brian Lovin",
  "Dan Abramov",
  "Mackenzie Child",
  "Gil Huybrecht",
  "Vinay Nair",
  "Yash Lalchandani",
  "Anusha Shetty",
  "Jayesh Nambiar",
  "Prashant Kamble",
  "MDS",
  "DHH",
];

// shuffle the people array
const shuffledPeople = PEOPLE.sort(() => Math.random() - 0.5);
---

<section class="px-5 py-50 flex flex-col gap-50">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-10 gap-4">
    <h1
      class="text-6xl/none col-span-full leading-tight tracking-tight font-medium"
    >
      <span class="block">Colophon</span>
      <span class="text-base-5 block">A note on how this site is made.</span>
    </h1>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-10 gap-4">
    <aside class="col-span-4 flex flex-col gap-10">
      <div
        class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide font-medium flex flex-col gap-2.5"
      >
        <p class="text-base-5">Type</p>
        <p>Inter — Rasmus Andersson</p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide font-medium flex flex-col gap-2.5"
      >
        <p class="text-base-5">Build</p>
        <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2.5">
          <li>Astro</li>
          <li>Tailwind CSS</li>
          <li>TypeScript</li>
          <li>Svelte</li>
          <li>GSAP</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div
        class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide font-medium flex flex-col gap-2.5"
      >
        <p class="text-base-5">Approach</p>
        <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2.5">
          <li>Static-first</li>
          <li>Editor Design</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </aside>
    <div class="col-span-5 flex flex-col gap-5 text-pretty text-lg">
      <p>
        This site exists to present work without interference. It avoids trends,
        unnecessary movement, and decorative systems that compete with content.
      </p>

      <p>
        The design relies on typography, spacing, and structure. Inter was
        chosen for its neutrality and clarity across screens—quiet, dependable,
        and designed to disappear. Layouts are simple by intent; interaction is
        restrained and purposeful.
      </p>

      <p>
        The site is built with a static-first mindset, prioritising performance,
        accessibility, and long-term maintainability. Tooling is modern but
        conservative. Every dependency earns its place.
      </p>

      <p>
        Over the years, I’ve been influenced by family, teachers, colleagues,
        designers, writers, musicians, and public figures—some personally, some
        from a distance—who have shaped how I think, work, and build.
      </p>

      <ul class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2.5 mt-15 text-base-5">
        {shuffledPeople.map((person) => <li>{person}</li>)}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
